crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ARMv7 ELF binary is a variant of the Mirai IoT botnet. It exhibits several definitive malicious behaviors: it implements a multi-vector DDoS suite (including HTTP, TCP SYN/ACK, and various UDP floods), an automated Telnet scanner for lateral movement using default credentials, and a process 'killer' module designed to remove competing malware from the infected host by scanning /proc and killing processes associated with specific ports. The malware ensures a single instance by binding to port 25081 (0x61f9), hides its process name using prctl, and communicates with a Command and Control (C2) server. It also includes routines to prevent system reboots by interacting with the hardware watchdog (/dev/watchdog).
